  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Despite the widespread use of total hip and knee arthroplasty, there is a notable lack of
      consensus regarding postoperative treatment, mostly because of the lack of well-designed
      studies testing the efficacy and effectiveness of such practices. In particular, there are no
      evidence-based recommendations on the amount of weight that the patient should be advised to
      bear on the operated leg after the operation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
